Responsecommentary

–block


You are the second person who mentions an excessive number of crosslinks, so I decided to remove the most egregious ones. The reasoning for them was twofold: first, I'm the kind of person who likes to wiki-walk, and I usually open the links in separate tabs to read them later. I forgot to consider that not everyone does the same, whoops. The second reason is tied with the name of the SCP ( the idea, out of universe, was for people to speculate about the true nature of the tower by offering several false leads. (Note that a certain spoilery GoI is not mentioned at all in the main text and only appears explicitly in the hidden collapsible).

To note, the removed crosslinks are: SCP-3882 as well, but since that phrase from Lockhart explicitly references the events there, I've decided to keep that one for now.

Each floor we get to see is dedicated to a specific GoI. The reason for Islam to be grouped together with Christianity and Judaism is that the corresponding floor is dedicated to the Horizon Initiative.

I suppose I'm too used to avoid contractions when writing academic-esque texts and that slipped to the video transcript, which isn't an academic text at all. I've tried to make it somewhat better, thanks for pointing it out. (I had the opposite problem with an early version of a paper I was working on)




I'm glad that this seems to work for most of the people who have commented here. Once again, thank you for the criticism as well if there is something else that can be done to improve this, I'll be glad to read about it.







